Sentencas: Electrolyte thin films of yttria-stabilized- zirconia (YSZ) for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell applications are investigated.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Films of same thickness and composition are fabricated by using two distinct thin film deposition techniques, atomic layer deposition (ALD) and radio frequency (RF) sputtering.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopic images indicate that both methods form uniform, polycrystalline films on amorphous matrix.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Deposition rates of ALD and sputtered YSZ electrolyte films are easily controllable.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In-plane ionic conductivity of O2- ions for YSZ is measured using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Experimental results show that, at a low temperature of 250A degrees C, ALD YSZ thin films exhibit considerably lower resistance to the conduction of oxygen ions as compared to the sputtered films.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This lower resistance results in better ionic conductivity of ALD YSZ thin films.
Titulo: Characterization of atomic layer deposited and sputtered yttria-stabilized-zirconia thin films for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
